Titolo: Astro Blaster

Anno: 1981

Descrizione: Astro Blaster is a fixed shooter released in arcades by Sega in 1981. It was designed and programmed by Gary Shannon and Barbara Michalec. It uses speech synthesis and during attract mode a voice says "Fighter pilots needed in sector wars...play Astro Blaster!" It is the first video game to have a copyright registered in Japan.

Genere: Fixed shooter

Valutazione: N/A
